<task id="013" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-08 Extract `RichFilePreview` renderer core from `RichFilePreviewDialog`</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G2 (parallel with 012; depends on Phase 1 ✅; unblocks 018, 022)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Phase 1 ✅</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, react-19, refactor, shared-lib</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extract the renderer core from the existing
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx`
    into a NEW reusable primitive `RichFilePreview.tsx` in the same shared library
    (`@spaarke/ui-components`). The extracted renderer hosts the iframe + 2-column
    body grid + metadata pane (Tags + Details) + Prev/Next nav + 3-dot
    `DocumentRowMenu` UI. The existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` is then refactored to
    be a thin wrapper that mounts the extracted renderer inside Fluent v9
    `Dialog`/`DialogSurface`/`DialogActions` chrome (modal use case unchanged).

    This task EXTRACTS only — it does NOT rebuild a parallel preview component. Per
    R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 the prohibition on a "parallel file-preview component to
    `RichFilePreviewDialog`" is explicit: implementer MUST extract (move shared
    rendering logic out, refactor the dialog to wrap it), MUST NOT author a parallel
    implementation. Acceptance criteria below VERIFY extraction (existing consumers
    untouched; same props, same visual output, same behavior).

    Downstream:
    - Task 018 (D2-09) `FilePreviewContextWidget` consumes the extracted renderer
      directly (non-modal Context-pane mount).
    - Task 022 (D2-08 follow-on) upgrades the R4 `DocumentViewerWidget` stub to
      consume the extracted renderer for Workspace destination. That upgrade is
      EXPLICITLY OUT OF SCOPE for this task — task 022 is a separate ticket and
      depends on this task.

    This task touches frontend TypeScript only — zero BFF code changes, so the BFF
    publish-size budget is NOT consumed by this task.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 19 expertise. Deep
    familiarity with refactoring large component files into composable primitives
    without breaking existing prop API, semantic-token dark-mode parity, and
    component-library boundary discipline in `@spaarke/ui-components`. Equally
    comfortable reading the existing `RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx` end-to-end before
    moving any lines.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreview.tsx`
    exists as a NEW reusable renderer that hosts the iframe + 2-column body grid +
    metadata pane (Tags + Details) + Prev/Next nav + 3-dot `DocumentRowMenu`
    chrome — i.e. every visual + interactive element of the existing dialog EXCEPT
    the modal `Dialog`/`DialogSurface`/`DialogActions` envelope. The existing
    `RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx` is refactored to import + mount `RichFilePreview`
    inside the modal envelope; its props API is unchanged; every existing consumer
    (LegalWorkspace, DocumentRelationshipViewer, SemanticSearchControl PCF, Office
    Add-ins) compiles + renders + behaves identically. New + existing tests pass.
    Dark-mode visual parity verified. `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates
    pass at Step 9.5.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/plan.md</file>
