    <file purpose="file-preview-barrel">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/index.ts</file>
    <file purpose="shared-lib-barrel">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (CRITICAL)">MUST EXTRACT the renderer from `RichFilePreviewDialog`. MUST NOT build a parallel file-preview component. R5 reuse mandate explicitly prohibits "parallel file-preview component to `RichFilePreviewDialog` (extract renderer, don't rebuild)". Acceptance criteria below verify extraction (not rebuild).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (backward compatibility)">Every existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` consumer (LegalWorkspace `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, DocumentRelationshipViewer `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, SemanticSearchControl PCF `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, any Office Add-in consumer) MUST continue to compile and render with NO prop API change and NO behavioral change. Dialog props (`IFilePreviewDialogProps`) remain stable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 + dark-mode parity. Extracted renderer MUST use Fluent v9 semantic tokens (`tokens.colorNeutralStroke2`, `tokens.colorNeutralBackground2`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1/2/3`, etc.) — NO hard-coded color literals. Dark-mode rendering MUST match light-mode visual hierarchy.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 — extracted renderer is a function component; uses `React.FC`/hooks; no React 18-only APIs introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Extracted renderer placed in `@spaarke/ui-components` shared library (`src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/`), NOT in `@spaarke/ai-widgets`. Both UI Components consumers AND AI Widgets consumers (task 018 `FilePreviewContextWidget`, task 022 `DocumentViewerWidget`) MUST be able to import it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">No PCF control change in this task. R5 has NO PCF controls per project CLAUDE.md §4.3.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029">BFF publish-size — this task is frontend-only (zero BFF code change). Confirm publish-size delta = 0 MB in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7">Test obligation — this task modifies a `@spaarke/ui-components` file. Add new co-located `__tests__/RichFilePreview.test.tsx` covering the extracted renderer; verify existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` test coverage (if any) still passes; if no existing dialog tests exist, add a minimal back-compat smoke test for the dialog wrapper too.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 task scope">Task 022 (DocumentViewerWidget upgrade) and task 018 (FilePreviewContextWidget) are SEPARATE tasks. This task ONLY extracts the renderer + refactors the dialog wrapper. Do NOT modify `DocumentViewerWidget.tsx` or create `FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` in this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">3-dot menu — reuse existing `DocumentRowMenu` (12 actions) imported from `../DocumentRowMenu`. Do NOT introduce a parallel menu component. `disabledActions` logic transfers as-is from the dialog (preview / aiSummary / toggleWorkspace / rename hidden by default; findSimilar hidden when no callback) but is parameterized at the renderer boundary so non-modal consumers can override.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Keyboard nav — the existing `ArrowLeft`/`ArrowRight` document-level keydown listener for Prev/Next must move to the extracted renderer. The listener's input-focus guard (`INPUT`/`TEXTAREA`/`SELECT`/`contentEditable`) MUST be preserved exactly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Effects + state — the iframe-load lifecycle (loading/error/retry state, `previewUrl` fetch on open or `documentId` change) MUST move to the extracted renderer unchanged. Reset-on-close semantics MUST be preserved at the renderer level (renderer behavior is identical regardless of whether the parent is a modal dialog or a non-modal pane).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>frontend/fluent-ui-v9/component-extraction</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006-pcf-and-ui.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-component-libraries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-ui-v9-dark-mode.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-react-19.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentRowMenu/index.ts</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Extract renderer, wrap with dialog" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx">
        The existing component cleanly separates concerns: the `Dialog` /
        `DialogSurface` / `DialogActions` envelope (modal chrome) vs. the title-bar
        + 2-column body grid + metadata pane + iframe + nav + 3-dot menu (the
        renderer). Extract the renderer as `RichFilePreview` exposing the props
        currently consumed by the JSX subtree below `&lt;DialogSurface&gt;`
        (documentName, documentId, documentType, createdBy, createdAt, fileSize,
        fetchPreviewUrl, onOpenFile, onOpenRecord, onEmailDocument, onCopyLink,
        onToggleWorkspace, isInWorkspace, onFindSimilar, onFetchSummary,
        navigationTotal, currentIndex, onNavigate, `disabledActions` override).
        Keep the `open` + `onClose` props on the DIALOG wrapper only — the
        renderer itself is open/close-agnostic. Move `useStyles`, helper
        functions (`formatDate`, `formatFileSize`, `nonEmpty`), the `useEffect`s
        for preview-URL fetch + keyboard listener, and the `handleRowAction` +
        `disabledActions` computation into the renderer.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Dialog wraps extracted renderer" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx (post-refactor)">
        After extraction, `RichFilePreviewDialog` becomes a thin function
        component: maps its `open`/`onClose` props onto Fluent's `Dialog`
        `open`/`onOpenChange`, forwards every remaining prop to
        `&lt;RichFilePreview {...rendererProps} /&gt;` inside
        `&lt;DialogSurface&gt;`, and supplies the `DialogActions` footer (Close
        button). Surface-clamp styling (1280px max-width, 85vh height) stays on
        the dialog wrapper or moves into a `surface` prop on the renderer —
        choose the cleanest seam during implementation and document the decision
        in task notes.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Shared-lib barrel export" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/index.ts">
        After extraction, the barrel must export `RichFilePreview` +
        `IRichFilePreviewProps` ALONGSIDE the existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` +
        `IRichFilePreviewDialogProps` exports. Existing exports MUST NOT change
        name or shape. Optional: a `disabledActions` type alias can be exported
        if downstream consumers (tasks 018, 022) need it.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Co-located tests" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/**/__tests__/*.test.tsx">
        Co-locate the new `RichFilePreview.test.tsx` under
        `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/__tests__/`.
        Mirror the testing-library + jest pattern used by adjacent component test
        files (e.g. `SprkChat/__tests__/SprkChatActionMenu.test.tsx`).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R4 stub `DocumentViewerWidget` (task 022's upgrade target) and the new R5
      `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) both need the rich file-preview UX
      (iframe + metadata pane + Prev/Next + 3-dot menu) WITHOUT the modal `Dialog`
      envelope. The existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` is the canonical
      implementation already promoted to `@spaarke/ui-components` and consumed by
      LegalWorkspace + DocumentRelationshipViewer + SemanticSearchControl PCF +
      Office Add-ins (see component file's header comment, lines 1–34). Authoring
      a parallel preview component would (a) duplicate ~900 LOC of polished UI +
      a11y + dark-mode work and (b) directly violate the R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE
      §3.1). Extraction is the correct path: pull the renderer out as a shared
      primitive, refactor the dialog into a thin wrapper, and let new R5 consumers
      mount the renderer directly in non-modal contexts.

      The 2-column body grid + metadata pane + 3-dot menu logic is mature
      (multiple rounds of UAT feedback baked in — title-bar nav placement, scrollbar
      hiding, grid-collapse fixes for the iframe mount). Preserving the existing
      visual output + a11y is the success bar for this task.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="Phase 1" status="complete">Phase 1 — Platform Extensions. Phase 1 gating per plan.md (BFF clean; session-files index provisioned; FieldDelta back-compat; cleanup job; tests pass; publish-size delta &lt; +0.5 MB).</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 018 (D2-09) `FilePreviewContextWidget` — DEPENDS on this task. Consumes the extracted `RichFilePreview` for non-modal Context-pane mount; single + multi-file rendering; per-file 3-dot menu wiring.</item>
      <item>Task 022 (D2-08 follow-on) — DEPENDS on this task. Upgrades R4 `DocumentViewerWidget` stub from R4 placeholder to the real extracted renderer. EXPLICITLY a separate ticket per `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`.</item>
      <item>Existing dialog consumers (NOT modified by this task; back-compat verified): `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, `src/client/code-pages/DocumentRelationshipViewer/src/components/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/components/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, plus any Office Add-in consumer.</item>
      <item>Component-library boundary: `@spaarke/ui-components` (shared lib; this task) vs. `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (AI-widget destination wrappers; tasks 018, 022 live there). Per ADR-012 the renderer belongs in the shared component library so both libs can import.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, run `context-handoff` and request `/compact`
      before starting. Declare RIGOR LEVEL per R5 CLAUDE.md §4.1:
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Frontend code change + shared-library refactor + back-compat
