         018 + 022.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 0 → 10 per task-execute SKILL.md;
         quality gates at Step 9.5 (code-review + adr-check).
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 013 status is 🔲, wave is P2-G2,
      parallel-safe = true, dependencies = Phase 1 ✅. Read `current-task.md` to
      confirm no conflicting R5 task is in flight. Confirm task 022 (DocumentViewerWidget
      upgrade) status is 🔲 (will be unblocked by this task) — do NOT pull task
      022 work into this task.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. SPECIFICALLY:
      read `RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx` end-to-end (it's the source you're
      extracting from). Map every section of the file to its destination:
      `useStyles` → renderer; helper functions (`formatDate`, `formatFileSize`,
      `nonEmpty`) → renderer; `useEffect`s + state → renderer; `handleRowAction` +
      `dialogDisabledActions` → renderer (with override prop); `Dialog` /
      `DialogSurface` / `DialogActions` envelope → stays in dialog wrapper.
      Read ADR-021 (semantic tokens) + ADR-022 (React 19) for hygiene reminders.
      Read R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate AGAIN — extraction is the explicit
      requirement; rebuild is the explicit prohibition.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan Extraction Boundaries">
      Document the seam in task notes:
      - `RichFilePreview` props (the renderer): documentName, documentId,
        documentType, createdBy, createdAt, fileSize, fetchPreviewUrl,
        onFetchSummary, onOpenFile, onOpenRecord, onEmailDocument, onCopyLink,
        onToggleWorkspace, isInWorkspace, onFindSimilar, navigationTotal,
        currentIndex, onNavigate, plus optional `disabledActions?:
        DocumentRowAction[]` so non-modal consumers can override which menu
        items hide.
      - `RichFilePreviewDialog` props (the wrapper): unchanged. Adds `open` +
        `onClose` on top of the renderer's prop set. Renders `&lt;Dialog&gt;` +
        `&lt;DialogSurface&gt;` + `&lt;RichFilePreview /&gt;` + `&lt;DialogActions&gt;
        (Close button)`.
      - Surface-clamp styling decision: keep dialog-specific surface CSS (max
        1280px × 85vh) on the dialog wrapper; the renderer is layout-agnostic so
        non-modal consumers control their own container size.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Create RichFilePreview.tsx (extracted renderer)">
      Create
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreview.tsx`.
      Move into it:
      - All `useStyles` rules from the dialog EXCEPT the `surface` rule (dialog-only).
      - All helper functions (`formatDate`, `formatFileSize`, `nonEmpty`).
      - The `IFilePreviewDialogSummary` interface (re-export from this file; the
        existing `RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx` re-exports become re-exports of the
        renderer's definition).
      - The component body from `RichFilePreviewDialog` MINUS the `&lt;Dialog&gt;`/
        `&lt;DialogSurface&gt;`/`&lt;DialogActions&gt;` envelope. Output is a plain
        `&lt;React.Fragment&gt;` (or top-level `&lt;div&gt;`) containing: title-bar
        (with optional Prev/Next + `DocumentRowMenu`), 2-column body grid (iframe
        + metadata pane). Footer (Close button) is OMITTED here — that lives in
        the dialog wrapper.
      - The preview-URL fetch `useEffect`, the keyboard listener `useEffect`, the
        `handleRetry`/`handlePrev`/`handleNext` callbacks, the `target` + 3-dot
        menu wiring, and `renderPreviewArea` + `renderTagSection` +
        `renderDetailsSection` helpers — all move into the renderer.
      - The `dialogDisabledActions` constant moves into the renderer as a
        DEFAULT computed value, but expose `disabledActions?: DocumentRowAction[]`
        as an optional prop that overrides the default when provided.
      Export: `RichFilePreview` (component) + `IRichFilePreviewProps` (interface)
      + `IFilePreviewDialogSummary` (re-export). All exports use semantic Fluent
      v9 tokens — no hard-coded colors.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Refactor RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx to wrap RichFilePreview">
      Refactor the existing
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx`
      to:
      - Keep `IFilePreviewDialogProps` interface UNCHANGED (back-compat).
      - Body becomes: `&lt;Dialog open onOpenChange&gt; &lt;DialogSurface
        className={styles.surface}&gt; &lt;RichFilePreview {...rendererProps}
        /&gt; &lt;DialogActions className={styles.footer}&gt;&lt;Button
        appearance="primary" onClick={onClose}&gt;Close&lt;/Button&gt;&lt;/DialogActions&gt;
        &lt;/DialogSurface&gt; &lt;/Dialog&gt;`.
      - Retain ONLY the dialog-specific styles (`surface`, `footer`).
      - Existing `displayName = 'RichFilePreviewDialog'` preserved.
      Verify the refactor by running a `tsc --noEmit` against the shared library
      and confirming no new errors.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Update barrel exports">
      Update
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/index.ts`
      to ALSO export `RichFilePreview` + `IRichFilePreviewProps` (alongside the
      existing `RichFilePreviewDialog` + `IRichFilePreviewDialogProps` exports).
      Verify
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts` (top-level
      barrel) — if it re-exports the FilePreview folder, no change needed; if it
      enumerates exports, add the new ones.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Back-Compat — Existing Consumers Unaffected">
      For each existing consumer found via repository search:
      - `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`
      - `src/client/code-pages/DocumentRelationshipViewer/src/components/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`
      - `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/components/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`
      - Any other `RichFilePreviewDialog`-importing file surfaced by `Grep`.
      Confirm: (a) import statement unchanged; (b) prop usage unchanged; (c) no
      TypeScript errors after refactor. Run `tsc --noEmit` across the affected
      packages. Capture results in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Add tests for RichFilePreview + back-compat smoke for dialog">
      Create
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/__tests__/RichFilePreview.test.tsx`
      with the following coverage (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7):
      - Renders title bar with documentName.
      - Renders iframe when `fetchPreviewUrl` resolves to a URL.
      - Renders loading spinner during fetch; renders error + Retry when fetch returns null.
      - Renders Prev/Next nav when `navigationTotal &gt; 1` + `currentIndex` + `onNavigate` provided; hides when omitted.
      - ArrowLeft/ArrowRight keydown dispatches Prev/Next; respects INPUT-focus guard.
      - Metadata pane renders Tags + Details with formatted date/size.
      - 3-dot menu opens; respects default `dialogDisabledActions`; honors override `disabledActions` prop.
      - `onFindSimilar` absent → `findSimilar` hidden in menu; present → visible + dispatches.
      If
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/FilePreview/__tests__/RichFilePreviewDialog.test.tsx`
      does NOT exist, add a minimal back-compat smoke test that mounts
      `&lt;RichFilePreviewDialog open ... /&gt;`, verifies the dialog surface
      renders, the renderer subtree mounts, and the Close button dispatches
      `onClose`.
      Run `npm test -- RichFilePreview` (or the workspace test command) and
      confirm all new + existing tests pass.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Dark-mode visual parity check">
      Render both `RichFilePreview` (standalone) and `RichFilePreviewDialog` in
      light + dark themes via the existing component sandbox / storybook /
      LegalWorkspace dev page. Capture screenshots or visual diff vs the
      pre-refactor dialog (light + dark). Verify: borders, backgrounds, foreground
      colors, hover states, focus rings, and the 3-dot menu's open menu all
      respect Fluent v9 semantic tokens identically in both themes. No
      hard-coded color literals slipped in during extraction. Record evidence in
      task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new + modified files
      (`RichFilePreview.tsx`, refactored `RichFilePreviewDialog.tsx`, updated
